Move it! Let's go!

1412
02:04:59,033 --> 02:05:01,618
SANDERSON:
All right, hold it up.
Hold it up.

1413
02:05:02,953 --> 02:05:04,954
SANDERSON:
Let's go! Move, move!

1414
02:05:05,748 --> 02:05:07,749
[GUNFIRE]

1415
02:05:07,917 --> 02:05:09,751
[SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

1416
02:05:19,470 --> 02:05:22,347
[MUSIC]

1417
02:05:59,260 --> 02:06:01,010
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

1418
02:06:01,178 --> 02:06:03,805
WADDELL:
Get down ! Get down !

1419
02:06:04,807 --> 02:06:06,307
WADDELL:
Get down, lady!

1420
02:06:08,644 --> 02:06:12,313
I'm out of ammo!
Sanderson, I'm out of ammo!

1421
02:06:18,153 --> 02:06:19,988
KURTH:
Don't you do it.

1422
02:06:20,155 --> 02:06:22,198
What are you doing?
Don't you damn do it.

1423
02:06:24,827 --> 02:06:26,160
YUREK:
Kurth, let's go!

1424
02:06:38,757 --> 02:06:40,008
[GAGGING]

1425
02:06:52,730 --> 02:07:10,538
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1426
02:07:21,216 --> 02:07:24,218
[MUSIC]

1427
02:07:38,233 --> 02:07:40,902
[LAUGHING]

1428
02:07:50,371 --> 02:07:53,581
[MUSIC]

1429
02:08:02,341 --> 02:08:04,258
[CROWD CHEERING]

1430
02:08:16,939 --> 02:08:19,816
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1431
02:08:42,965 --> 02:08:45,133
[COUGHING]

1432
02:08:49,972 --> 02:08:51,973
SOLDIER 9:
Easy. Easy.

1433
02:09:31,180 --> 02:09:32,180
[LAUGHS]

1434
02:09:41,023 --> 02:09:43,065
Ah, shit.

1435
02:09:43,233 --> 02:09:45,359
Bullet missed your jugular
by about three millimeters.
Don't move!

1436
02:09:45,527 --> 02:09:46,527
All right.

1437
02:09:48,405 --> 02:09:50,865
Hurry up, hurry up.

1438
02:09:51,033 --> 02:09:53,117
SANDERSON:
Grimes?

1439
02:09:54,286 --> 02:09:58,122
Little short on coffee,
but I got you some tea.

1440
02:10:01,877 --> 02:10:04,712
How you doing, soldier?

1441
02:10:04,880 --> 02:10:06,714
Can't feel a thing.

1442
02:10:07,591 --> 02:10:10,259
[MUSIC]

1443
02:10:49,091 --> 02:10:50,091
STEELE:
Ruiz.

1444
02:10:51,677 --> 02:10:54,595
Hey, Sergeant. Hey.

1445
02:10:57,933 --> 02:11:00,268
Captain.
Lorenzo.

1446
02:11:00,435 --> 02:11:02,436
How you doing?

1447
02:11:04,565 --> 02:11:09,360
It went in and out, so the medic
said I should be okay,
a couple of days.

1448
02:11:09,528 --> 02:11:13,447
That's great news.
We going after them?

1449
02:11:13,615 --> 02:11:16,492
You bet your ass we will.
We got to regroup.

1450
02:11:17,995 --> 02:11:20,329
Don't go out without me.

1451
02:11:20,497 --> 02:11:24,667
Don't go back out there
without me.

1452
02:11:24,835 --> 02:11:27,837
I can still do my job.

1453
02:11:28,881 --> 02:11:31,591
You get some rest now, okay?

1454
02:11:46,690 --> 02:11:48,024
You going back in?

1455
02:11:49,860 --> 02:11:51,861
There's still men out there.

1456
02:11:54,197 --> 02:11:56,657
Goddamn.

1457
02:12:00,913 --> 02:12:03,205
When I go home,

1458
02:12:03,373 --> 02:12:06,584
people ask me, "Hey, Hoot,

1459
02:12:06,752 --> 02:12:08,836
why do you do it, man?

1460
02:12:09,004 --> 02:12:12,840
Why? You some kind
of war junkie?"

1461
02:12:13,008 --> 02:12:16,052
I won't say
a goddamn word.

1462
02:12:16,219 --> 02:12:18,220
Why?

1463
02:12:18,388 --> 02:12:21,599
They won't understand.

1464
02:12:21,767 --> 02:12:24,018
They won't understand
why we do it.

1465
02:12:25,687 --> 02:12:29,649
They won't understand
it's about the men next to you.

1466
02:12:31,652 --> 02:12:34,445
And that's it.

1467
02:12:35,030 --> 02:12:36,614
That's all it is.

1468
02:12:45,415 --> 02:12:49,001
Hey, don't even
think about it, all right?

1469
02:12:49,169 --> 02:12:51,587
I'm better on my own.

1470
02:12:55,342 --> 02:12:59,387
Hey, we started
a whole new week.
It's Monday.

1471
02:13:03,100 --> 02:13:05,017
[CHUCKLES]

1472
02:13:07,145 --> 02:13:08,604
[DOGS BARKING]

1473
02:13:12,317 --> 02:13:16,237
EVERSMANN:
I was talking to Blackburn
the other day and he asked me,

1474
02:13:16,405 --> 02:13:19,115
"What changed?
Why are we going home?"

1475
02:13:20,784 --> 02:13:23,119
And l said, "Nothing."

1476
02:13:23,286 --> 02:13:27,999
But that's not true, you know.
l think everything's changed.

1477
02:13:28,750 --> 02:13:30,084
l know l've changed.

1478
02:13:35,841 --> 02:13:38,384
A friend of mine asked me
before I got here--

1479
02:13:38,552 --> 02:13:40,928
When we were all shipping out.

1480
02:13:41,096 --> 02:13:43,723
He asked me,

1481
02:13:43,890 --> 02:13:47,101
"Why are you going to fight
somebody else's war?

1482
02:13:47,269 --> 02:13:49,854
What do y'all think,
you're heroes?"

1483
02:13:52,649 --> 02:13:56,027
I didn't know what to say
at the time, but. . .

1484
02:13:58,113 --> 02:14:00,614
if he asked me again,
I'd say no.

1485
02:14:03,160 --> 02:14:06,037
I'd say there's no way in hell.

1486
02:14:06,204 --> 02:14:08,831
Nobody asks to be a hero.

1487
02:14:13,420 --> 02:14:15,796
It just sometimes
turns out that way.

1488
02:14:19,593 --> 02:14:22,762
I'll talk to your ma and pa
when I get home, okay?

1489
02:14:26,308 --> 02:14:30,728
[MUSIC]

1490
02:15:05,263 --> 02:15:07,098
RUIZ:
"My love,

1491
02:15:07,265 --> 02:15:11,018
you're strong
and you'll do well in life.

1492
02:15:11,186 --> 02:15:14,438
l love you
and my children deeply.

1493
02:15:14,606 --> 02:15:19,235
Today and tomorrow,
let each day grow and grow.

1494
02:15:19,402 --> 02:15:24,782
Keep smiling and never give up,
even when things get you down.

1495
02:15:24,950 --> 02:15:27,493
So, in closing, my love,

1496
02:15:27,661 --> 02:15:31,247
tonight,
tuck my children in bed warmly.

1497
02:15:31,414 --> 02:15:33,249
TeII them I Iove them,

1498
02:15:33,416 --> 02:15:38,754
then hug them for me
and give them both
a kiss good night for Daddy."

1499
02:15:40,882 --> 02:15:44,718
[MUSIC]

